Privacy Policy
Effective Date: December 16, 2024
Weather Fit (“we,” “our,” or “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy
          Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use the Weather Fit application
          (“Weather Fit” or “Application”). By using the Application, you consent to the practices described in this
          Privacy Policy.
Information We Collect
We collect and use the following information to provide, understand, and improve Weather
          Fit:
User Interaction Data
Distinct IDs and anonymized device IDs.
Usage of Weather Fit features (e.g., total sessions, session length).
Preferences for outfit categories (e.g., hats, scarves).
Application settings (e.g., language, region, wardrobe settings).
Technical data such as iOS version, device model, and app version.
Location Data
Your device’s location to provide localized weather forecasts and outfit suggestions.
If location access is disabled, the app may not provide personalized weather predictions.
Subscription Information
Details about your active or expired subscription plans for Premium features.
Aggregated Data
Anonymized statistics about app usage, such as how many users access specific features.
How We Use Your Information
Provide accurate weather forecasts and personalized outfit suggestions.
Improve user experience through analytics and feedback.
Offer relevant features based on your preferences.
Process subscription payments and manage trial periods.
Communicate updates or changes to the Application.
Third-Party Services
To enhance functionality, Weather Fit integrates with third-party services that may
          collect, process, or store certain data. These services include:
AdMob
(ads)
Mixpanel
(analytics)
Mapbox
(mapping features)
RevenueCat
(subscription management)
Sentry
(error tracking and crash reporting)
Each service has its own Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review these policies to understand their
          practices. Weather Fit does not control or assume responsibility for the actions of these third-party
          services.
Cookies and Tracking
Weather Fit does not directly use cookies. However, third-party services like AdMob may
          use cookies or similar tracking technologies for personalized ads. Additionally, Weather Fit requests App
          Tracking Transparency (ATT) permission during the first app launch, which you can manage via your device
          settings.
Data Sharing and Privacy
Weather Fit takes your privacy seriously. We adhere to strict data protection standards as
          outlined in our Privacy Policy.
Consent to Share Consumption Data with Apple
By using our app and making in-app purchases, you consent to our sharing of data regarding
          your usage and consumption of purchased content with Apple, as part of our efforts to resolve refund requests.
          This information may include details about how you have accessed and interacted with the purchased content.
          Such data sharing is done in compliance with Apple’s policies.
Location Data Usage
If you grant access to your device’s location:
We use it to provide weather forecasts and outfit suggestions.
Location data is anonymized and not stored permanently.
You can disable location sharing through your device’s settings.
Data Security
We implement industry-standard measures to secure your information. However, no system can
          guarantee absolute security. By using Weather Fit, you acknowledge that data transmission over the internet
          carries inherent risks.
Data Retention
We retain your information only as long as necessary for operational purposes. Aggregated,
          anonymized data may be retained indefinitely for analytical purposes.
Data Sources and Accuracy
Weather Fit integrates with multiple weather providers, including Apple Weather, Xweather,
          and AccuWeather. While we strive for accuracy, discrepancies may occur due to differences in provider data. We
          do not guarantee the availability or accuracy of forecasts.
International Data Transfers
Weather Fit processes and stores data using third-party services that may be located
          outside your country. By using the Application, you consent to the transfer, storage, and processing of your
          information in countries where data protection laws may differ from your local laws.
Third-Party Links
The Application may include links to third-party websites or services. Clicking these
          links may direct you to their platforms, which have their own privacy policies. Weather Fit is not responsible
          for the practices or content of third-party services.
Aggregated Data Collection
We may collect anonymous, aggregated statistics (e.g., feature usage rates) to improve the
          Application. This information cannot identify you and is considered non-personal data.
App Updates and Termination
Weather Fit may require updates to maintain compatibility with iOS or improve
          functionality. By using the Application, you agree to install updates as needed. We reserve the right to
          discontinue the Application or certain features at any time. Upon termination, you must cease using the
          Application.
Your Rights
Request deletion of your data by contacting us at
hi@weatherfit.com
.
Access or update your stored information.
Privacy Policy Updates
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in the Application,
          third-party services, or legal requirements. Continued use of Weather Fit after updates constitutes your
          acceptance of the revised terms.
Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact
          Anton Chuiko at
hi@weatherfit.com